President Trump held a meeting in the Cabinet Room with various leaders and individuals affected by drug addiction to discuss the opioid crisis in the United States. He highlighted the importance of preventing drug abuse, strengthening law enforcement, and increasing access to treatment and recovery services. Several individuals shared their personal stories of addiction and recovery, emphasizing the need for greater awareness, understanding, and support for those affected by drug addiction. The President expressed his commitment to addressing the issue and announced plans to take action to combat the opioid epidemic.